### Gitter is the home of many developer communities...

Gitter is home to over 25,000 developer communities. By the makers of GitHub, this free public service allows unlimited users, unlimited history and unlimited integrations. 

For private teams or communities, it's free for up to 25 users and just $5 per user for larger teams.

I'm having a hard time deciding whether I like Slack or Gitter more. I use both, but for different things. Slack has a great API and is great for their easy to configure integrations, but it seems to be more for private teams.

All you need to chat on Gitter is a GitHub account, so it's a great place to get questions answered about specific code repositories. Each repository has the capability to have a Gitter chat room along with it. If you want to put it on your blog, then all you have to do is copy this tiny bit of JavaScript and you're set.

```
<script>
  ((window.gitter = {}).chat = {}).options = {
    room: 'sethbergman/ghost-blog'  };
</script>
```
<script src="https://sidecar.gitter.im/dist/sidecar.v1.js" async defer></script>

  <script>
    ((window.gitter = {}).chat = {}).options = {
      room: 'sethbergman/ghost-blog'    };
  </script>

